
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [strings.replace] slot to replace occurrences of a specific substring within a string. It retrieves the value of the [start] argument from the [.arguments] node and uses it as the replacement target. The [strings.replace] slot is invoked with the [@.result] expression, indicating the string to be modified, and the [get-value] slot fetches the replacement string from the arguments.
strings.replace:x:@.result
   .:[[start]]
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/start
